content.detailedDescription:
i was looking out the window in my kitchen early one a.M. when a particularly bright star caught my eye. it was e.S.E. in the sky above the tree tops in my back yard.
 i had recently bought a digital camera and unencumbered by the price of film i used it regularly. i got the camera and began to video tape the star, mostly to check out the capabilities of my new toy. then i snapped  a few stills, zooming in and out etc. 
 it wasn't until several months later, when my memory  was full( my camera mem.) that i started clearing out all the images that i'd saved. when i got to the star photos, which by the way i'd totally forgotten, i decided to see  just how close i could zoom in. i played back the video, freezing it on the images that were not  blurred by my movements and began to zoom in. 
 i was shocked to find what was there.
 the shape alone was peculiar. then i looked a little deeper, i saw something enshrouded by the glow. inside of it.
 i sent these images earlier this year to you guys but never heard back from any one.I would sure like any input you might have.
 i'm a 40 year old totally sane male. i never gave much thought to aliens beyond thinking that the universe was much to vast to be home to only earth.
 look froward to any response.
 john birmingham
content.summary: Star gazeing with new camera.

content.detailedDescription:
I was walking my dogs. saw point of light ( nw ) ufo way overhead. out stretched arm, fingertip reference, it moved in an arc to the sw in less than 90 seconds more than four feet, changed course slightly, slowing down dramatically,then picked the speed back up and did not go into the horizon rather off into higher space until faded from view.More details upon request.
i checked all known resources for satellite, iss and hubble activity. none even remotely close.
content.summary: Star like point of light high speed slowed down changed course

content.detailedDescription: I was swimming in my cousins yard. that's when i heard a carnival ride noise and turned around, that's when i saw a big triangle shaped thing flying over my cousins neighbors house. i didn't know what the heck it was. it was a triangle shape. it had round edges and was flat on bottom and top. the object was making a whooshing noise and had red lights on each corner on the bottom. i can't remember if it had a white light in the middle, i think it did. it was moving very slowly and very close to the ground. i was shocked and excited. i called my cousin and we watched it together. it went behind and tree and we never saw it again.
content.summary: Triangle with round edges red lights on bottom of  each edge

content.detailedDescription:
I was in wildwood nj over the fourth of july weekend 1980 or 1981 - i think the sighting was in 1981. i was waiting for everyone to get ready to go out, i was on the front porch of a rented house, looked up the street and saw this gigantic blimp shaped object hovering just over the electric lines. it was around dusk, not night-time. the object had multi-colored lights outlining it, i can't remember if they were on all the time, or blinking. it was partially obscured by buildings, and was between our house and the beach, about a block and a half from the beach. i swear i watched this thing for a good 20 minutes, no one else saw it. it just sat there in the sky. i had no feelings of "oh wow,i have to tell someone about this!", and in hindsight, i'm surprised i had no reaction to seeing this thing.And no, it was not a blimp, or a plane, or planes, it was unidentified.

i went back inside at some point - the weird thing is, i forgot all about this event until years later, maybe 10 years later. totally forgot it. makes it even more bizarre.

now i've done a little research and i believe that it is the same ufo referred to as the hudson valley ufo. i've seen a photo of that one that is pretty identical to the object i saw.
content.summary: Hovering blimp shape with multi-colored lights around edges

content.detailedDescription: I was in the pool sunday afternoon. i asked my oldest son to get me something to drink. when he return i looked up at him to say thank you and to get my drink. high in the sky but directly over his head i saw what seemed to be a silver cylinder object moving about the same speed lightening would move leaving a streak behind it.As it passed over head and out of my view, my old son and youngest son spotted it. almost at the same time we all said did you see that?
content.summary: Lightening like ufo witness by 3 different people at the same time

content.detailedDescription:
My fiance, close friend and i were walking down skiview lane in leaveworth, wa about 10pm when we noticed a light in the south similar in size to a star (it remained this sze throughout the sighting) moving erraticly and slightly flashing different colors. i believe it at first to be a planet with the clouds moving in front of it (there was partial cloud cover). but the movements were nothing like i could identify so we tried to decide if it could be a plane or helicopter. but it was moving in circles and in horizontal dips that were smooth, fast and like nothing i've ever seen. in addition to the movement it had lights that seemed to sit at the sides of the star like point of light, but did not flash and were about a quarter of the saze of the main light. the main light went through gradual patterns of blue, white and green. it seemed to move toward the mountains and the west slowly while continuing it's movements. my friend and i then noticed, much like you are able to see the dark side of the moon at night, that the object was chevron shaped. my fiance did not see this, but he wears contacts so it may have obstructed his ability to see it. as i noticed the shape i realized we could only make it out because the object was closer. i got fairly upset and wanted to go back to the house. it seemed to move off again. we went to the house, a three minute walk, and sat on the lawn. the object had moved further off west and continued its movements. we could see it was moving for sure now because we had the trees at my parents house as a reference point. my friend and i then noticed these lines of very very faint circles of light, in lines of maybe five coming off of the object and moving away. it also emmited these lights one at a time from the top and sides of the point of light at the seeming tip of the object. but not at the same time as the lines of light. my fiance stayed to watch the object while my friend and i got some binoculars. through the binoculars my friend and i could see that the chevron seemed to be made up of very dim beams of light coming off the tip. they were greensih colored and were like isoceles triangles, thicker at the tip and diminishing as they ran away from the main light. it was similar to how northern lights look. my fiance did not see this, but he was having a hard time focusing the binoculars. about this time we decided to go inside as we were cold and nervous and had been witnessing the event for over an hour. 
i don't know what to think of the event, i do not really believe that aliens are coming here... it's very hard to describe the movements of this object, this is what convinced me it was not normal. these movements i can hardly describe, and have fairly rattled my views on the subject of ufos.
content.flightPath: Stationary,Path with directional change,Path then hovering,Other
content.summary: Small light at "tip", possible lights coming off sides indicating chevron; small lights released from it.

content.detailedDescription:
i was 12 years old at the time of these ufo events. in my small town of paris tennessee. these objects were seen by untold numbers of people in my town. it last for three days some in the news media. were saying these were metors.

        they were not metors by no chances. this very bright amber objecting would fly at great speed. then stop in midflight and stay in one spot for more then ten mins or more. then othr bright amber objectings were all doing the same manuver. going from spot to spot in the heavens. it just did not making any logical sense. this has always be a great mystery to me. it was not just a few amber like objects do this manuver. i could not count th numbers of objects. going from one spot and stoping and another objecting a great speed doing the same thing. stoping at great speeds like it was lineing up. this story ran in our local newspaper. no one has every said what these objects were.
content.flightPath: Stationary,Hovering then path,Straight-line path,Path with directional change,Path then hovering
content.summary: in june the eleventh i saw many ufos

content.detailedDescription: I was driving home from work on rt 16 approaching the turn off to hanover (same place as an earlier sighting)and looked to my right. there was an object hovering over the trees. i couldn't make out the shape--could only see the lights. there was a white light in the center with pulsing red lights on either side. after turning towards hanover i could still see it in my rear view mirror and watched until i went over the hill where the high school was. i drove the remaining 3 miles home, told my mom about it and persuaded her to go with me to see if it was still there. it was still in the exact place i had last seen it but as soon as we started to drive in that direction it started to move away from us--almost like it could read our minds and knew we were chasing it. we followed it for a while but we could never get any closer to it so we turned around. when we got back to the top if the hill we could still see it in the moving slowly in the distance.
content.summary: Ufo hovering over trees

content.detailedDescription: I stay up late at night in my backyard and i sit outside to smoke and i always look at the stars. for the past six years ive seen plenty of planes from the tulsa area and i see a lot of commercial flights but every so often i see a light that looks like a star traveling in different directions and at different speeds and different times always at night very high up i would guess 30,000 feet or better no flashing lights solid light  i always look for anything moving in the night sky different movement they just seem to appear and i watch them until they disappear not sure what it is i know we have satalites but these must be huge to see from the ground that high up just not sure what they are. my wife and i both have seen them
content.summary: Star like object  different directions different times

content.detailedDescription: in either 1967 or 68, my father, neighbor, and i were going to play golf at henry horton state park. we were on 31e, heading into madison tn., when a glowing silverish red object, tree top high, crossed the highway in front of us. it looked as if it had just entered the earths atmosphere. the glow looked similar to a nasa module that is red hot on the fringe of the craft but shiny silver in the center during re-entry. the craft definitely had a fuselage because of the glowing blue flame that was emitted from the rear and clearly visible compared to the glowing area in the front. the shape was similar to a light bulb but more teardropped in the front. it was actually similar to staring at a light bulb on its side.  you could see the parameters of the outside but the glow restricted the sharp outside edge of the craft, except in the rear. it was approx. 30 ft long and 8 ft high. the craft crossed the highway parallel to the ground from south to north and disappeared over the trees to the north. it made no noise, but the bunson burner like blue flame flickered from the rear of the craft at the same pace as the approx. 30 mph speed it was traveling.  it was viewed by us to be an ufo from the very beginning.   i am a retired aerospace tooling liaison engineer and i worked 5 years, at nasa, on the us space station. i know what we witnessed was real.  after we returned home, on the nightly news, metro police had chased one and there was some sixty sightings in georgia.
content.summary: Approx. 100 ft off the ground, it crossed the highway approx. 300 ft in front of us.

content.detailedDescription: Was driving thru town, noticed the clouds around the sun turned rainbowish, took a few pictures of the sun, then took a few more of the scenery.  upon developing the picture, i noticed a silver triangle type object in the top right.   when zoomed in, the object appears to have three balls of light on the bottom.    not sure if it is dust from the windshield, but it seems to be catching the light from the sun.

content.detailedDescription: I was waiting for the bus on midway and washington avenue in escondido and i noticed these objects in the distance and they were over by grand avenue...They looked like little round objects because they were so far away but then they started to hover and their lights started to blink...Then they split into three groups and started rising into the atmosphere...I turned away concerned and i told my brother to look and we were both puzzled at what they were...We turned to get on the bus for a split second and we turned back and they were nowhere to be found...
content.summary: Cluster of round objects

content.summary: Star like ufo in sky (golden, co)

content.detailedDescription:
At the time i lived at bonneville dam on the oregon side and was sleeping out side in the summer heat. it was late, perhaps 1 am and i was looking at the stars and then noticed a illuminated ring that appeared over the mountain on the oregon side of river. the craft  was completely silent as it floated about the tree tops about 1.5 miles away. the ring then started to pulsate and slow down until there where several lights that where rotating slowly in one direction and then spin in the opposite direction.
i watched for about a minute as the craft floated about, staying in the general area that it first appeared.
next i heard the sound of a helicopter approaching. the craft then moved and disappeared behind the mountain top and the sound of the helicopter faded.   
i was young at the time and very frightened. i tried to wake the other kids that where outside however everyone was asleep and did not see it in time.

looking back on this experience many years latter i think it is possible that the craft could have been a helicopter with strobe lights on the tips of the rotor blades, however i do not know how it could have remained silent.
content.summary: Rotating ring of lights flew over mountain top

i ask my self what could it be it wasn't a plane, it's didn't look like a ballon i mean to say there was no basket on it. i didn't know what it was and i had no i dea what it could be. it was floating it just kinda drifted away to to the right of me. i was shocked i had never seen anything like it i mean balloons upside down rain drops this looked more like a coke can than any thing and it was way to low to be a ballon. i was very surprized. 
but the wind was blowing in to where i was standing.
i whent in after four or six mins. of looking at it because i didn't want to get in truble 
and i still don't know what it is.
i didn't have a photo cuz i was at work and i never carry my camera to work but never again.

content.detailedDescription: On my way home from work, heading east on rt 16 from newark, i was near my turn off to hanover when i glanced over to the right of the highway and saw 2 large shining spheres hovering  above the tree line. they were so bright that they illuminated the woods below. suddenly a ray of light shot out of one of them and struck the other knocking it back slightly. then they quickly flew off side-by-side in the direction of the radio tower in newark. i've never seen anything accelerate that fast. from the to the time it took off til it disappeared over the horizon took only about 3 seconds.
content.summary: 2 large shining spheres

content.detailedDescription: The pictures were taken in sequence by a wildlife cameral on june 19, 2008. this camera takes pictures daily and we have several files of wildlife pictures using this camera with no previous anomalies. there were 33 pictures taken june 19-june 20, 2008. the event pictures began with image 18,june 20, 2008 at 4:29 a.M., where a deer is looking back toward the tree line where the object was photographed. picture 19 shows the image of the cylindrical object at about a 45 degree angle. this object was stationary and did not appear to be moving. unfortunately, i tried to enhance the object by zooming in, and ended up cropping the picture so the deer was not visible. however the cylider is very clear in this picture. image 20 was taken at 4:46 a.M. with the deer and the object is clearly visible in the background, still at about a 45 degree angle on the tree line and it had not moved. image 21 still has the object in the same place, however i tried to zoom in and cut out the deer. image 22, taken at 5:05 a.M. shows the deer, but the object has moved and is in a horizontal position. there is also a white light to the right of it, however that may be a drop of water on the lense of the camera. image 23, taken at 5:46 a.M. shows just the deer. the cylindrical object is gone. i am including images 24,25,& 26 because they show the background and the tree line. this camera is stationary and is never moved. i am only able to submit images 19,20, & 22.
content.summary: Pictures taken with wildlife camera. rural area

content.detailedDescription: Wife and i were driving down randall mill road at gateway park when both of us notice bright disk through trees up and forward of us. being an airline employee i first assumed the object to be a commercial airline with the sun reflecting off of its aluminum fuselage coming in for an approach to a local airport. i would guess object was 2,000 feet asl and it did not show any airspeed. the object was bright for one of the three seconds that we saw it and then for the two remaining seconds was a dark gray disk. the craft cloaked and became invisible after that so we pulled over to get out of the car to maybe hear or see the craft reappear but with no such luck
content.summary: Very bright disk

content.detailedDescription: I took a picture of the moon on a cloudy night sky and again after tweaking the setting on the camera.  days later i downloaded the photos to my laptop to see what looks like an ufo is on the first (cloudy) photo to the lower right side.

content.detailedDescription: The object hovered and darted about for 16 minutes at an altitude of approximately100 ft. from the ground,the object was an unusually bright blue and its outline was clear and distictive making no noise what soo ever. strangly enough,what drew my attention to the the object was the feeling of static in the air that raised the hairs on my arms and neck and what could only be described as the feeling of walking through a giant magnetic chamber as to the waves of magnetic resonanance that i felt when the thing first got my attention. the object was like an elongated tear drop shape that didn't alter orin any way and as i stated earlier, it would dart off in one direction then come to a dead stop from a blazing speed with out slowing down and then wouldjust as suddenly change direction some times without even stopping.
content.summary: For almost 16 minutes the object hovered and darted at an altitude of about 100 feet until it took of at a right angle from a dead hover to almost light speed and disappeared over the mountains.
